name: What Makes A Loyal Customer?
description: The notion of the ‘loyal customer’ has been described as a ‘threatened species’. Commitment to a brand is considered anachronistic, and programs to support loyalty are regarded by some critics as doomed ventures. But I would argue that customer loyalty has been getting a bad rap. And part of the reason for this is that marketers have approached customer loyalty the wrong way, and have focused on locking customers in, rather than attracting new markets.

name: Exploring Pilots' Experiences of Integrating Technologically Advanced Aircraft Within General Aviation: A Case Study
description: For doctoral dissertation, utilized a case study with three embedded participants' groups to explore the impact of technologically advanced aircraft on general aviation based on technological determinism by comparing the findings between private pilots, commercial and instrument rated pilots, and certified flight instructors to examine technological innovations affect on aviation safety and pilots' decision-making skills.
